==English==

===Etymology===
First attested in the 1570s. From {{der|en|fro|accoster}}, from {{der|en|VL.|accosto||to come alongside someone}}, from {{m|la|ad||near}} + {{m|la|costa||rib, side}}. Cognate with {{cog|es|acostar||to lie down, go to bed}}.

